Battery Type: The test batteries used are Prismatic Cells.

Nominal Capacity: 1100 mAh

Testing Description: All CS2 batteries followed the same charging profile, which is a standard constant current/constant voltage (CC/CV) protocol: they were charged at a fixed constant current rate until the voltage reached 4.2V, and then the voltage was maintained at 4.2V until the charging current dropped below 0.05A. Unless otherwise specified, the discharge cut-off voltage for these batteries was 2.7V. All CS2 batteries were randomly numbered and named accordingly. The n-th numbered CS2 battery is named "CS2_n".

Cycling Conditions:

CS2-33 and CS2-34 were cycled at a constant current of 0.5C.

CS2-35 to CS2-38 were cycled at a constant current of 1C.

Data Storage: The charging segment data for the batteries under these two operating conditions have been organized into two separate .mat files, respectively.
